<h2>Nav lists</h2>
<p>A simple and easy way to build groups of nav links with optional headers.</p>
<p>Take a list of links and use the <code>w-nav-list</code> tag to create a <a href="/api/havok/widget/NavList.html">havok/widget/NavList</a>.</p>

<h3>Markup nav list Example</h3>
<p>If using markup, add <code>class="nav-header"</code> to create headers:</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="well" style="max-width: 340px; padding: 8px 0;">
        <w-nav-list>
            <li class="w-nav-header">List header</li>
            <a class="active" href="">Home</a>
            <a href="">Library</a>
            <a href="">Applications</a>
            <li class="nav-header">Another list header</li>
            <a href="">Profile</a>
            <a href="">Settings</a>
            <hr />
            <a href="">Help</a>
        </w-nav-list>
    </div>
</div>
